message.content:
Below is one way to “read off” the two finished towers from the photos and match them block‐by‐block to the dictionary.  I have broken the description into two parts (left structure, then right structure), followed by the exact list of which dictionary blocks are needed and a possible step‐by‐step assembly order.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  LEFT‐HAND STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Overall Count & Layers  
  – Uses 4 total blocks in 3 vertical layers.  
  – Layer 1 (floor): Two orange cylinders standing upright side‐by‐side.  
  – Layer 2: One long yellow rectangular prism laid horizontally across the two cylinders.  
  – Layer 3: A single orange triangular “roof” block sitting on top of the yellow prism.

• Matching Dictionary Blocks  
  – Orange cylinders (vertical) match block #8 in the dictionary.  
  – Long yellow rectangular prism (horizontal) matches block #7.  
  – Orange triangular roof matches block #12 (in the same orientation shown in the dictionary).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  RIGHT‐HAND STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Overall Count & Layers  
  – Uses 7 total blocks arranged in 4 layers.  
  – Layer 1 (floor): Two red “arch” blocks side by side (one with the curved opening left‐to‐right, the other front‐to‐back).  
  – Layer 2: One green rectangular prism laid horizontally on top of the arches.  
  – Layer 3: One long yellow rectangular prism (horizontal), spanning the green block.  
  – Layer 4: An upright orange cylinder in the center with two orange triangular roof blocks flanking it.

• Matching Dictionary Blocks  
  – Red arch with opening left‐to‐right is block #3.  
  – Red arch with opening front‐to‐back is block #1.  
  – Green horizontal bar is block #4.  
  – Yellow horizontal rectangular prism is again block #7.  
  – Orange vertical cylinder is block #8.  
  – Each orange triangular roof piece is block #12 (two identical copies).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  COMPLETE LIST OF BLOCKS NEEDED
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• #1  (red arch) × 1  
• #3  (red arch) × 1  
• #4  (green rectangular prism, horizontal) × 1  
• #7  (yellow rectangular prism, horizontal) × 2  
• #8  (orange cylinder, vertical) × 3  
• #12 (orange triangular roof) × 3  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

{  
  Step1: Move block with index 8        // first orange cylinder for left tower  
  Step2: Move block with index 8        // second orange cylinder for left tower  
  Step3: Move block with index 7        // yellow prism on top of those two cylinders  
  Step4: Move block with index 12       // orange triangle roof for left tower  

  Step5: Move block with index 1        // red arch (front‐to‐back) for right tower base  
  Step6: Move block with index 3        // red arch (left‐to‐right) next to it  
  Step7: Move block with index 4        // green horizontal block on top of red arches  
  Step8: Move block with index 7        // yellow horizontal prism above the green block  
  Step9: Move block with index 8        // orange cylinder standing above the yellow block  
  Step10: Move block with index 12      // first orange roof piece on right tower  
  Step11: Move block with index 12      // second orange roof piece on right tower  
}

This builds both the left and right structures exactly as shown, using only the dictionary orientations given (no rotations).
